		</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->
		
		<div class="comment-body"><p>Abraham Lincoln’s Enduring Legacy</p>
<p>* He did everything in his wisdom and power to avert Civil War.</p>
<p>* He succeeded in preserving the Union and kept it from suffering irreparable fragmentation.</p>
<p>* He,  and a post war congress, ended the immoral and destructive institution of slavery throughout the United States forever, via, the emancipation proclamation and the thirteenth amendment.</p>
<p>* He called for a peaceful and humane plan in the restoring of southern states back into the union. </p>
<p>* He bequeathed to Americans, and all mankind,  a rich heritage of the most inspirational and eloquent oratory ever spoken or penned by a U.S. president.</p>
<p>Abraham Lincoln in Perspective:</p>
<p><a href="https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&#038;pid=explorer&#038;chrome=true&#038;srcid=0B7lAWzevz5aKM2YwZWM3ZGUtMWQ3NC00ZWNkLWE4ZTktMTlkZjNiMmVjMWI0&#038;hl=en_US" rel="nofollow ugc">https://docs.google.com/viewer?a=v&#038;pid=explorer&#038;chrome=true&#038;srcid=0B7lAWzevz5aKM2YwZWM3ZGUtMWQ3NC00ZWNkLWE4ZTktMTlkZjNiMmVjMWI0&#038;hl=en_US</a></p>
