		<div class="comment-body"><p>Apparently the Abraham Lincoln haters of the following web site (and similar sites) don&#8217;t like opposing and challenging points of view, so I must take their article and my response elsewhere to their shame. It really is an eye opener, as it reveals that those who hate always do a couple of basic things: They distort facts, or skew them; and they censure comments to their liking.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.squidoo.com/abraham-lincoln" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.squidoo.com/abraham-lincoln</a></p>
<p>My response to that article which was censured out:</p>
<p>Jackson once lifted his glass in the midst of antagonists and proclaimed, &#8220;The Union! It must be preserved!&#8221; and then he walked out. I lift my glass to Abraham Lincoln and say,  &#8220;To his beloved memory, it must be preserved among all Americans!&#8221;</p>
